Based on the principles of HCI, a good web design should present a user-friendly web interface to access the information they need.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="1" relname="elaboration"> A user-friendly web interface should make web users feel easy to access the information that web users need.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="8" relname="span"> Also, usability is another important criteria to measure </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="3" relname="condition">if a web page/site is a good web page/site.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="9" relname="span"> A good web page/site should deliver the best and the most current information for web users.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="4" relname="antithesis"> Without this premiss, no texts, fonts, colors, images, audio/video components, programming, web servers, and databases can play their roles in a good web design.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="10" relname="summary"> 
To sum up, Usability, Accessibility, User-friendly, Quality, and Performance should become the essential criteria to measure a good web design.</segment>
